{
  "texts": [
    "Agent parameters, including the learning rate α and discount factor γ, are configured as 0.01 and 0.9, respectively.",
    "To improve search efficiency, we restrict the maximum number of exploration steps to 300 within each episode.",
    "For a better exploration of the environment, Q-learning uses the ϵ-greedy method for agent training, allowing a probability of ϵ to randomly select actions:",
    "where π act (s) is the exploration policy under state s. Equation (6) represents the ϵ-greedy algorithm, exploring with a probability of ϵ and exploiting with a probability of 1-ϵ.",
    "In the early stage of model training, increased exploration is necessary to find the target."
  ]
}